                "text": "<p>We make it easy to find the tech you love. Our platform brings together trusted electronics, gadgets, and laptops from leading global brands, so you can shop smarter and faster.</p><p><strong>Last updated: July 20, 2025</strong></p><p><strong>Shopowave</strong> operates this store and website, including all related information, content, features, tools, products, and services, in order to provide you, the customer, with a smooth and secure shopping experience (the \"Services\"). Shopowave is powered by Shopify, which enables us to provide these Services to you. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose your personal information when you visit, use, make a purchase or other transaction through the Services, or communicate with us. If there is a conflict between our Terms of Service and this Privacy Policy, the Privacy Policy governs with respect to personal information.</p><p>Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By using and accessing any of the Services, you acknowledge that you have read and understand the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described herein.</p><h4>Personal Information We Collect or Process</h4><p>When we say \"personal information,\" we mean any data that can identify or be linked to you. This may include:</p><ul><li><strong>Contact details</strong>: name, shipping and billing address, phone number, email address.</li><li><strong>Financial info</strong>: payment details, transaction history.</li><li><strong>Account data</strong>: username, password, preferences.</li><li><strong>Order history</strong>: viewed items, cart contents, purchase and return records.</li><li><strong>Support interactions</strong>: messages or communications with our team.</li><li><strong>Device info</strong>: IP address, browser, device type, cookies.</li><li><strong>Usage patterns</strong>: time on site, clicks, and feature usage.<br/><br/></li></ul><h4>How We Collect Personal Information</h4><p>We collect personal data:</p><ul><li><strong>Directly from you</strong> when you browse, buy, register, or contact us.</li><li><strong>Automatically</strong> through cookies, pixels, or your device.</li><li><strong>From partners</strong> and service providers such as payment processors and delivery services.</li><li><strong>From third-party platforms</strong> you use to interact with our Services.<br/><br/></li></ul><h4>How We Use Your Personal Information</h4><p>We use your personal information to:</p><ul><li>Process your purchases, manage accounts, and fulfill orders.</li><li>Provide customer service and support.</li><li>Send updates, offers, and personalized marketing (if you’ve opted in).</li><li>Prevent fraud and ensure platform security.</li><li>Improve the Services and user experience.</li><li>Comply with legal requirements.<br/><br/></li></ul><h4>How We Share Your Personal Information</h4><p>We may share information with:</p><ul><li><strong>Shopify</strong>, our platform provider.<br/></li><li><strong>Third-party vendors</strong>, including payment processors, logistics, and analytics tools.</li><li><strong>Marketing and business partners</strong>.</li><li><strong>Legal authorities</strong> if required.</li><li><strong>Affiliates</strong> or <strong>successors</strong> in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale.<br/></li></ul><h4>Shopify’s Role</h4><p>Our Services are hosted by Shopify. Your data may be stored or processed by Shopify in various locations, possibly outside your country. Please review<a href=\"https://www.shopify.com/legal/privacy\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Shopify’s Privacy Policy</span></a> for more details.</p><h4>Links to Other Websites</h4><p>We may link to third-party websites not under our control. We are not responsible for their privacy practices. Please read their policies before sharing any information.</p><h4>Children’s Privacy</h4><p>Shopowave is not intended for use by children under the legal age of majority. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If a child’s data is discovered, we will take steps to delete it.</p><h4>Data Security and Retention</h4><p>We use safeguards to protect your personal data but cannot guarantee complete security. We retain your data only as long as necessary to provide our Services, meet legal obligations, and resolve disputes.</p><h4>Your Rights</h4><p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to:</p><ul><li>Request access, correction, or deletion of your personal data.</li><li>Withdraw marketing consent.</li><li>File a complaint with a relevant data protection authority.<br/></li></ul><p>Requests can be made via email. We may verify your identity before processing.</p><h4>International Data Transfers</h4><p>Your information may be transferred across borders. When transferring from the EU/UK, we use safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses.</p><h4>Changes to This Policy</h4><p>We may revise this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted here with the latest date.</p><h4>Contact Us</h4><p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please reach out:</p><p><strong>Shopowave</strong> Email: support@shopowave.com Phone: +880 1234 567890</p>",
